<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link 
  href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" 
  rel="stylesheet" 
  integrity="sha384-EVSTQN3/azprG1Anm3QDgpJLIm9Nao0Yz1ztcQTwFspd3yD65VohhpuuCOmLASjC" 
  crossorigin="anonymous"
  >
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/terminal.css@0.7.2/dist/terminal.min.css" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/terminal.css@0.7.1/dist/terminal.min.css" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/terminal.css@0.7.1/dist/terminal.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/welcome.css">
</head>

<body class="terminal">
  <header class="p-3 bg-dark text-white">
    <%- include('../partials/home-nav') %>
    
  </header>

<main class="bg-light">
  <div class="container py-5 px-3">
    <div 
      class="row row-cols-2 row-cols-md-3 row-cols-lg-4 row-cols-xl-5 g5 g-sm-3 g-xxl-5 px-sm-5 px-4">
        <div class="col">
          <!-- user clicks on profile to edit profile from this view thats why this is an a link -->
          <a class="text-decoration-none" href="/profiles/<%= profile._id %>">
            <div class="card shadow-sm">
              <% if (profile.avatar) { %>
                <img
                  class="card-img-top"
                  src="<%= profile.avatar %>"
                  alt="<%= profile.name %>'s avatar"
                  width="100%"
                  height="auto"
                />
              <% } else {%>
                <img
                  class="card-img-top"
                  src="/images/icons/user.png"
                  alt="A placeholder avatar"
                  width="100%"
                  height="170"
                />
              <% } %>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p class="card-title fs-5 text-dark mb-0">
                  <%= profile.name %>
                </p>
                  <% if (user.profile._id.toString() === profile._id.toString()) { %>
                  <a class="text-decoration-none" id="editBtn" href="/profiles/<%= profile._id %>/edit">
                      <button class="error">Edit Profile</button>
                  </a>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <a class="text-decoration-none " id="logoutBtn" href="/auth/logout">
                      <button class="btn btn-danger">Logout</button>
                  </a>
                   <% } %>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section class="welcome-slides" id="welcome-screen">
    <br>
    <div class="jumbotron">
      <br>
      <p class="lead" id="welcome-text">Welcome to the Timeline Variance Authority virtual database tour. As a software engineering fellow at General Assembly, you've been hand-picked to join us in managing our infinite database of timeline variants in preparation for the Multiversal War! You will be assigned an employee badge to begin this tutorial on how to manage top-secret files about a select group of variants. You'll be able to view details about known variants and their aliases. Keep in mind, these files are top-secret so you'll only be able to view select pieces of data. This minimal tour of our database prepare you for your new role as an agent at the Timeline Variance Authority. For All Time. Always.</p>

      <hr class="my-4">

      <p class="lead">First, you'll need to create your own variant tracker list. Then you'll navigate to our top-secret database to see if we have already started tracking your potential variants!</p>
      <br>
      <a href="/variants"class="btn btn-primary btn-lg startBtn" id="startBtn" role="button">Let's Get Started!</a>
    </div>
</section>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
